 :tx/rationale "DS-CHECKPOINT: PASSIVE checkpoint thread — WAL to .edn conversion without blocking reads or writes. Inspired by FrankenSQLite's PASSIVE checkpoint mode. ARCHITECTURE: Background thread reads WAL entries since last checkpoint marker. For each entry: serialize TxFile to EDN, compute BLAKE3 hash, write to txns/shard/hash.edn, fsync. After all entries processed: write checkpoint marker (WAL byte offset) so next checkpoint starts from there. PASSIVE: Never blocks the commit thread or read threads. Reads WAL entries that are already fsynced — no race with the commit thread. FULL CHECKPOINT: Triggered by braid harvest --commit or explicit braid checkpoint command. Same as PASSIVE but BLOCKS until all entries are flushed. Ensures all .edn files exist before git commit. TRUNCATE: After FULL checkpoint, optionally truncate WAL to reclaim disk space (WAL entries are now redundant with .edn files). INTERVAL: PASSIVE checkpoint runs every 1-5s (configurable via :config/checkpoint-interval-secs datom per C9/ADR-FOUNDATION-031). GIT SAFETY: At any time, .edn files represent a valid prefix of all transactions. The WAL tail may have entries not yet in .edn — these are durable (WAL fsynced) but not git-committable until next PASSIVE checkpoint completes."
